defaultThank you for your invitation to send in my views on cycling safety. These are my views. Whether this makes it evidence I don't know.
default&#xa0;
default1. Is Cycling, especially urban cycling safedefaultNothing totally safe in the real world. In fact urban cycling is safer on a
default per mile basis than rural cycling. I am told that cycling is about as safe per mile as being a pedestrian; 
defaultWe
default just worry about cycling more. As it puts up your life expectancy it can't be that dangerous. 69 or so pedestrians were killed in London last yea
defaultr. Has any fuss been made about that? Most of those who call cycling too dangerous seem just to want cyclists off the roads.
default&#xa0;
defaultOne oft-forgotten issue is that cycling along rural 
defaultA
default roads is particularly dangerous. Some thought should be given to installing 
defaultcycle-ways on these whenever building new ones. Here at least there are few pedestrians to clash with.
